DR. Chuck - Postgresql for everybody

Arquitectura SQL

Inicio Postgresql command line like SuperUser
============================================= 
sudo psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U postgres (password is postgres)
\l --> lista todas las bases de datos.
\q --> sale de la session actual.
\dt --> muestra las tablas que posee la base de datos a la que se esta conectado.
\d+ "nombre-de-la-tabla" --> muestra esquema y la estructura de la tabla indicada

Creando un usuario y Base de datos
==================================
CREATE USER barcvilla WITH PASSWORD 'b4000$.';
CREATE DATABASE people OWNER barcvilla ENCODING 'UTF-8';

Conectarse a la base de datos people
====================================
psql people barcvilla

Sentencias SQL
==============
INSERT INTO manufacturer (name, description) VALUES ('part 1', 'primer repuesto');
UPDATE manufacturer SET description='Arandel 5/8' WHERE manufacturer_id=1;
SELECT * FROM manufacturer WHERE manufacturer_id=1;
DELETE FROM manufacturer WHERE manufacturer_id=1;
SELECT * FROM manufacturer ORDER BY description;
SELECT * FROM manufacturer ORDER BY description DESC;
SELECT * FROM manufacturer WHERE name LIKE '%e%';

/*LIMIT ->> Obtenemos las 2 primeras filas*/
SELECT * FROM manufacturer ORDER BY name LIMIT 2;

/*OFFSET ->> Saltamos n filas y Obtenemos las 2 primera filas. OFFSET empieza desde 0 */
SELECT * FROM manufacturer ORDER BY name OFFSET 1 LIMIT 2;

ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN id SERIAL;
ALTER TABLE users ADD PRIMARY KEY(id);


